# This file is used to declare the required JDK version for this project.
# It is compatible with SDKMAN and is also recognized by IntelliJ IDEA.
# How to use:
# - Uncomment the desired Java version below.
# - On UNIX-based systems (Linux/macOS), SDKMAN can automatically install
# and switch to the specified JDK version via `sdk env install` / `sdk env`.

# - IntelliJ IDEA may also detect this file and suggest configuring or downloading the JDK.

# Important notes:
# - This file is intended to ensure all developers use the same JDK version.
# - Automatic setup works best on UNIX-like environments where SDKMAN is fully supported.
# - On Windows, behavior may be inconsistent (especially outside WSL),
# and automatic JDK installation/configuration in IntelliJ IDEA may not work as expected.
# - In such cases, install the required JDK manually and configure it in IDE settings.

# Example versions (uncomment one when needed):

# java=25-oracle
# java=26-open
# java=17.0.18-tem
